    slug: "the-muslim-creed-expounded-pocket-size",
    description: `The Muslim Creed Expounded (Pocket Size) is a concise yet comprehensive guide to Islamic aqeedah (creed and theology) that distills the essential beliefs every Muslim must hold into a compact, portable format. This pocket-sized edition makes the fundamental principles of Islamic faith readily accessible, allowing readers to carry it with them for daily reference, study, and revision. Despite its small size, the book covers all the essential components of correct Islamic belief with clarity and scholarly precision.

The book is structured around the six articles of faith that form the foundation of Islamic aqeedah: belief in Allah (His Lordship, His names and attributes, and His right to worship), belief in the angels (mala'ikah), belief in the divine scriptures (kutub), belief in the prophets and messengers (rusul), belief in the Day of Judgment (yawm al-qiyamah), and belief in divine predestination (al-qadar). Each article of faith is explained with supporting evidence from the Quran and authentic hadith, presented in a manner that is easy to understand without sacrificing accuracy.

In addition to the six articles of faith, the book addresses important creedal matters that are relevant to contemporary Muslims. These include the correct understanding of tawheed (Islamic monotheism) and its three categories — tawheed ar-rububiyyah (Lordship), tawheed al-uluhiyyah (worship), and tawheed al-asma wa as-sifat (names and attributes). The book also covers matters such as the position of the companions of the Prophet (peace be upon him), the concept of bid'ah (religious innovation), the intermediate position between extremes (the wasatiyyah approach), and common misconceptions about Islamic creed that have emerged in different Muslim communities.

The methodology of the book is firmly rooted in the understanding of the early generations of Muslims (the salaf as-salih), drawing primarily upon the Quran, the authentic sunnah, and the consensus of the scholars of Ahl as-Sunnah wal-Jama'ah. The author avoids sectarian polemics and instead focuses on presenting the agreed-upon fundamentals of Islamic creed in a clear and positive manner. Where differences of opinion exist among scholars on subsidiary creedal matters, these are noted with appropriate scholarly references.

The pocket-size format of this edition makes it particularly useful for students of Islamic knowledge who need a quick reference guide, for travelers who wish to maintain their study routine while on the move, and for anyone who prefers a concise summary of Islamic beliefs. It is also an excellent tool for da'wah purposes, as it provides a structured and evidence-based presentation of Islamic theology that can be shared with non-Muslims or Muslims who are new to formal Islamic education. The Muslim Creed Expounded (Pocket Size) fills an important need for a reliable, accessible, and portable guide to the fundamentals of Islamic faith.`,
    metaDescription: "A pocket-sized guide to Islamic creed covering the six articles of faith, tawheed, and essential beliefs. Concise, scholarly, and easy to carry."
