    slug: "the-night-of-decree",
    description: `The Night of Decree (Laylatul Qadr) is a beautifully illustrated and thoughtfully written children's book that introduces young readers to one of the most significant nights in the Islamic calendar. This engaging publication from Darussalam's children's collection explains the meaning, importance, and blessings of Laylatul Qadr — the Night of Power and Decree — in a manner that is accessible, age-appropriate, and spiritually uplifting for children.

The book opens by introducing the concept of Laylatul Qadr through the Quranic description in Surah Al-Qadr, which states that this single night is better than a thousand months. Using child-friendly language and vivid illustrations, the book explains that Allah chose this special night to reveal the Quran to Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) and that every year, this night returns during the last ten days of Ramadan with extraordinary blessings for those who worship Allah sincerely.

Throughout the pages, children learn about the key characteristics of Laylatul Qadr — that it falls in the odd nights of the last ten days of Ramadan (the 21st, 23rd, 25th, 27th, or 29th night), that the angels descend to the earth in multitudes, that it is a night of peace and tranquility until the break of dawn, and that the reward for worship on this night is beyond measure. The book encourages children to participate in seeking this blessed night by praying, making du'a, reciting the Quran, and engaging in extra worship during the last ten days of Ramadan.

The illustrations in the book are carefully designed to be engaging and culturally appropriate, depicting scenes of families worshiping together, children reading the Quran, mosques illuminated at night, and other imagery that helps bring the concepts to life. The artwork supports the text without contradicting Islamic principles regarding visual representation.

The book also includes practical guidance for children on how to make the most of the last ten days of Ramadan. It suggests simple du'as that children can memorize and recite, encourages them to set personal goals for worship and good deeds, and provides ideas for family activities that can make the search for Laylatul Qadr a meaningful and memorable experience. Parent-child interaction is encouraged throughout, with discussion prompts and activities that families can do together.

The Night of Decree serves as an excellent educational tool for parents and Islamic school teachers who want to teach children about the significance of this blessed night. The book's combination of clear text, beautiful illustrations, and practical guidance makes it suitable for children aged 5 to 10, though younger children can enjoy it with parental assistance. It is a valuable addition to any child's Islamic bookshelf and makes a wonderful Ramadan gift that can be enjoyed year after year as the family's understanding and practice of Ramadan deepens.`,
    metaDescription: "A beautifully illustrated children's book about Laylatul Qadr. Teach kids the significance of the Night of Decree with engaging stories and activities."
