    slug: "the-pillars-of-islam-iman",
    description: `The Pillars of Islam & Iman is a comprehensive and foundational book that provides a detailed explanation of all the pillars upon which the Islamic faith and practice are built. This essential work covers both the five pillars of Islam (Shahadah, Salah, Zakat, Sawm, and Hajj) and the six pillars of Iman (belief in Allah, His angels, His books, His messengers, the Day of Judgment, and divine predestination), presenting them in a clear, systematic, and evidence-based manner that makes this complex subject accessible to readers of all knowledge levels.

The book is organized into clearly defined sections, with each pillar receiving thorough treatment. The section on the pillars of Islam begins with the Shahadah (the declaration of faith), explaining its meaning, conditions, requirements, and the profound implications of testifying to the oneness of Allah and the prophethood of Muhammad (peace be upon him). The chapter on Salah (prayer) covers the significance of prayer in Islam, the prerequisites and conditions for valid prayer, the detailed procedure for performing the five daily prayers, the various types of prayers (obligatory, recommended, and funeral prayers), and common mistakes that should be avoided.

The chapter on Zakat (alms-giving) provides a comprehensive guide to Islamic charity, including the types of wealth subject to Zakat, the calculation methods, the categories of recipients, and the spiritual and social benefits of this pillar. The chapter on Sawm (fasting) covers the rules of fasting in Ramadan and voluntary fasting, the things that invalidate the fast, and the wisdom behind this important act of worship. The chapter on Hajj (pilgrimage) offers a step-by-step guide to performing the pilgrimage, including the rites of Ihram, Tawaf, Sa'i, standing at Arafah, and the days of Tashreeq.

The section on the pillars of Iman provides equally detailed coverage. The chapter on belief in Allah covers the concept of Tawheed in its three categories and the attributes of Allah as understood in Islamic theology. The chapter on angels discusses the nature, types, and functions of angels in Islamic belief. The chapters on divine books and messengers provide an overview of the scriptures revealed by Allah and the prophets sent to various nations throughout history. The chapter on the Day of Judgment covers the events of the Hereafter, including the resurrection, the accounting, and the ultimate destiny of human beings. The final chapter on divine predestination (al-qadar) explains this often-misunderstood concept with clarity and nuance.

Throughout the book, the author supports every point with evidence from the Quran and authentic hadith, ensuring that readers receive accurate and reliable information. The writing style is clear and methodical, making it suitable for use as a textbook in Islamic schools and study circles, as a reference guide for families, and as a self-study resource for individual learners. The Pillars of Islam & Iman is a must-have book that every Muslim household should contain, providing a solid foundation for understanding and practicing the essential tenets of the Islamic faith.`,
